{"id":"46de1cfc-22c9-44ae-8b42-af169271f839","timestamp":"2026-05-20T23:13:19.100Z","type":"gemini","content":"","thoughts":[],"tokens":{"input":17693,"output":60,"cached":14864,"thoughts":44,"tool":0,"total":17797},"model":"gemini-3-flash-preview","toolCalls":[{"id":"google_web_search_1779318799005_0","name":"google_web_search","args":{"query":"Jan AI Ollama integration guide"},"result":[{"functionResponse":{"id":"google_web_search_1779318799005_0","name":"google_web_search","response":{"output":"Web search results for \"Jan AI Ollama integration guide\":\n\nIntegrating Jan AI with Ollama allows you to use Ollama's efficient inference engine and extensive model library within Jan's polished desktop interface.[1]\n\n### Prerequisites\n1.  **Install Ollama:** Download it from [ollama.com](https://ollama.com).[2]\n2.  **Install Jan AI:** Download it from [jan.ai](https://jan.ai).[3]\n3.  **Run Ollama:** Ensure the Ollama service is running (usually starts automatically, or run `ollama serve` in your terminal).\n4.  **Download a Model:** Pull a model via terminal (e.g., `ollama pull llama3.1`).\n\n---\n\n### Method 1: Using the Built-in Ollama Extension (Recommended)\nModern versions of Jan include a dedicated Ollama extension that simplifies the process.\n\n1.  Open **Jan AI**.[4][5][3][6][2]\n2.  Go to **Settings** (gear icon in the bottom-left).[5]\n3.  Select **Extensions** from the sidebar.\n4.  Find the **Ollama** extension and click **Enable**.[7]\n5.  Once enabled, click on the extension settings and ensure the server URL is set to `http://localhost:11434`.\n6.  Go back to the **Hub** or **Models** tab. You should now see your local Ollama models listed.[4][5][6]\n\n---\n\n### Method 2: Manual Integration (OpenAI-Compatible API)\nIf the extension is not available or you prefer manual control, you can connect Jan to Ollama via its OpenAI-compatible endpoint.\n\n1.  Open **Jan AI** and go to **Settings**.[5][6]\n2.  Select **Model Providers**.[4][6]\n3.  Click on **OpenAI** (or \"Add Provider\" if you want a separate entry).[6]\n4.  Configure the following fields:\n    *   **API Key:** Enter `ollama` (Ollama ignores this, but Jan requires a value).[8]\n    *   **Base URL:** `http://localhost:11434/v1`[6][4][8][5]\n5.  **Add Your Models:**\n    *   In the **Models** section of the provider settings, click the **+ (Plus)** icon to add a custom model.[6]\n    *   Enter the **exact name** of the model as it appears in Ollama (e.g., `llama3.1:8b`). You can find this by running `ollama list` in your terminal.[6]\n6.  Save the settings.\n\n---\n\n### Method 3: Using the \"Engines\" Tab (Legacy/Advanced)\nIn some versions of Jan, you may need to add Ollama as a custom engine.\n\n1.  Go to **Settings** > **General** > **Engines**.[5][6]\n2.  Click **Install Engine** and enter:\n    *   **Engine Name:** `Ollama`\n    *   **Chat Completions URL:** `http://localhost:11434/v1/chat/completions`\n    *   **Model List URL:** `http://localhost:11434/v1/models`[6][5]\n    *   **API Key:** `ollama`[6][8][2][7][5][9]\n3.  Click **Install**.[5]\n\n---\n\n### Troubleshooting\n*   **Connection Refused:** Ensure Ollama is running. Try visiting `http://localhost:11434` in your browser; it should display \"Ollama is running\".\n*   **Model Not Found:** Double-check that the model name in Jan matches the output of `ollama list` exactly (including tags like `:latest` or `:8b`).\n*   **CORS Issues:** If Jan cannot connect, you may need to set the `OLLAMA_ORIGINS` environment variable to `*` and restart Ollama.\n    *   **macOS/Linux:** `OLLAMA_ORIGINS=\"*\" ollama serve`\n    *   **Windows:** Set `OLLAMA_ORIGINS` to `*` in System Environment Variables and restart the Ollama app.\n\nSources:\n[1] serverman.co.uk (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHjEsxVT9VnLMDdXB8EilEmZyLgfi5a-8jVHN_XKKAmbDNvkkTS5e-teeLXmsOaVB4_-R4iMJk6RqbLzNUiW2DQloD1Ujyx8rredbk4ACOWW-AeUZ_wbjKS7JORv9NBAF2VSQimwUQstWcwJnlxx2M=)\n[2] promptquorum.com (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEHM_qYUNYBUrXNUErcR4sWaZ_N3HSiCLoY1qedJgySKWYoxLL45v8u2xszT6rWzMz5fkx6BmaoHBZ7rB9-NADsmAh2ePtJuGE7QydEpTjnAEc4UyAJq4tNGjJu5J9eGrOzF9mBGSjORGk6uvI3fIvXlX2GHlhqB8IETNxGSlqaYQc=)\n[3] youtube.com (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH-ji6etSEIOY40eXDzHkwgQnxjN6u0VHEw6k4NQoHySjlmCUMBW9PPoa4fLC_3vj_PuTyasATgG7ugTtd2hBkOkP76jv-1CQSFf1DmIHarPKUlYDcvSWaLsQQ6Amqd-uvep9QotY0=)\n[4] reddit.com (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE9sguW2jhMhNuroezvnMs5ds-I_M6wQPYb1MnZoZhFgxGFI8ShJjyLmdCCCJm_tnNhciJ1ejPo4QeO_31UyZ8A3qgD00eRnQirbD7XRmKwZypgeH--ebUCowsWbuYBqlnNL5_gMcCTw_gR71fD1gwqnMzJEWGHwjPbrdv5MxLEKtxl1vSLirUxcPgDoWhF1J_o)\n[5] taylorbrazelton.com (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEDgg-S3l1evP44YDaCXpTkMPjvdtNu_Opa4K8eYVVUeXCZAfaykgOH4aiVWQU497rh88JXPlLneuwcBJFH-JfmWzIJweyAIlmN19ixTcrUdNuFBLHHHwdq3hpE7mbuFrs1qXpGvjj1eROHH-c1UmizpJSrtlE9TvE9ekhSx3cB95C5mtTuCZVGJLE7)\n[6] knowivate.com (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH_aLDMkQZbeEBIfWbzAshlsp_LgUnG3qRpl43wHCl_8vDgjDHPflwZQghJ6Py6nZWvm50fgXSRa6Mu2vVkoCWth5SJek6Zg49CJ7-wlr73pmLwyg8afZYKOBNBd_GNRDEfmrxvhYcwMx0Cy0rz_yMJQH1YUnas1hDaE-umKLgWRTrKTgvOC0BSNXTT)\n[7] localaimaster.com (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEvhv5vGPKs7KYPKoEXO_HjCEvwdjk9EC6nrZXwV0tW0LRLZCP9YDBMBuONFXSu6poTdiqwFBFkoXtcxEuAzr6vog1pqdedkLr265hWLTkHIk_-XFw1kJa0VbSSE4zb4n4ARfxhYO35U0JqDcxV-QPfup5U9g==)\n[8] dev.to (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHjzk-nbL9hRj38F1aa_9bFVGW7wiiNlwJUml_EIj5Qv6v2tY8M20KLTO9THLrJaQ9BAd5V0-VB-r3WksRN1WxZNBqY2HvTUDN0LfRBYqI7ULmJMrYLyfsu_RO6wY6xlM8Gncl-QHzMyfLZXbjoVoxeaXTZqVr4M87dXAQw4Nn6kIab7M7HlMymnCMa4XqIiWh_ww==)\n[9] youtube.com (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH7CGE1xfl3zM0D2_eAUFjQeqwS0mkxwHdVRYY67YXIemrvbEIA1pccf9ffG9WP2T