{"id":"30f09799-ed6e-4ddf-bda4-68bb30ead3e7","timestamp":"2026-05-20T23:23:30.844Z","type":"gemini","content":"The error `unknown model architecture: 'gemma4'` indicates that the version of Ollama you are currently running (**0.22.1**) is too old to understand the architecture of the model you're trying to use (`gemma-4-E4B-it-OBLITERATED`). \n\nThis is not a permission issue, but a compatibility issue with that specific model file.\n\n### Immediate Fix\nTry switching to one of your other models that use more standard architectures, such as:\n*   **`llama3.1:8b-instruct-q4_K_M`**\n*   **`llama3:8b-instruct-q4_K_M`**\n\nThese should work perfectly with your current setup.\n\n### Long-term Fix: Update Ollama\nSince we are in May 2026 and your system is running Ollama 0.22.1, you are likely using a very outdated version of the package. To use newer models like \"Gemma 4\" (or models using its architecture), you need to update your NixOS system or the specific Ollama package.\n\n1.  **Check for updates:**\n    ```bash\n    nix-channel --update\n    # OR if using flakes:\n    nix flake update /home/nondeus/.nix-config\n    ```\n2.  **Rebuild your system:**\n    ```bash\n    sudo nixos-rebuild switch --flake /home/nondeus/.nix-config\n    ```\n\nIf you want to continue using Jan with the current version, just select the **Llama 3.1** model in the Jan UI. It will load without the \"unknown architecture\" error.","thoughts":[{"subject":"Discovering Model Limitation","description":"My current Ollama version, 0.22.1, appears to be the bottleneck, as it doesn't recognize the 'gemma4' model architecture specified. This is likely the root cause of the 'unknown model architecture' error I encountered with `gemma-4-E4B-it-OBLITERATED`. I need to investigate upgrading Ollama to a more recent release to support this model.","timestamp":"2026-05-20T23:23:28.093Z"},{"subject":"Investigating Model Name","description":"I'm realizing the 'Gemma 4' in the model name might be a misinterpretation or a custom designation rather than an actual architecture. My Ollama version is quite outdated, likely preventing recognition of newer or uniquely named models. A version upgrade is a strong possibility.","timestamp":"2026-05-20T23:23:28.692Z"}],"tokens":{"input":38623,"output":369,"cached":34594,"thoughts":656,"tool":0,"total":39648},"model":"gemini-3-flash-preview"}
