{"id":"dec553a5-f42c-4032-a90c-ad7140c12027","timestamp":"2026-05-21T01:23:21.919Z","type":"gemini","content":"The systemd service errors you saw at the end of the rebuild were caused by a \"zombie\" process from the `asus-shutdown` service that refused to die, which in turn prevented the NixOS activation script from completing cleanly.\n\nI have resolved this by manually killing the hung process and restarting the service.\n\n### Summary of Improvements\n1.  **Ollama Fixed & Updated:** Ollama is now running version **0.23.1** (updated from 0.22.1). This version should have much better compatibility with the newer \"Gemma 4\" and \"Qwen 3.5\" models you have downloaded.\n2.  **CORS Allowed:** The `OLLAMA_ORIGINS=\"*\"` fix is still active and persisted in your `configuration.nix`. Jan AI can now communicate with Ollama without \"Forbidden\" errors.\n3.  **Kernel Updated:** You are now running **Linux Kernel 7.0.5-cachyos**, and the system rebuild successfully finished.\n4.  **Service Health:** All system services (including `asus-shutdown` and `ollama`) are now in a healthy \"active (running)\" state.\n\n### Final Check\n1.  **Open Jan AI.**\n2.  **Select a model** (Try `llama3.1` first to confirm basic functionality, then try your newer `gemma-4` or `Qwen3.5` models).\n3.  **Start chatting.**\n\nEverything is now synchronized and ready to use.","thoughts":[],"tokens":{"input":46336,"output":325,"cached":42618,"thoughts":0,"tool":0,"total":46661},"model":"gemini-3-flash-preview"}
