{"id":"13f271fd-b826-4db1-8ece-9641dfdd8c3b","timestamp":"2026-05-21T01:25:54.694Z","type":"gemini","content":"The \"Forbidden\" error is definitely gone, but the **\"unknown model architecture: 'gemma4'\"** error persists because even version 0.23.1 of Ollama is not new enough to support that specific model. \n\nSince it's May 2026 and \"Gemma 4\" appears to be a very recent release (or uses a custom architecture), we need to ensure you are on the absolute latest version of Ollama available in Nixpkgs.\n\n### 1. Verify a supported model works\nTo confirm your setup is otherwise perfect, please try selecting **`llama3.1:8b-instruct-q4_K_M`** in Jan AI. \n*   If this works, your Jan-to-Ollama connection is 100% fixed.\n*   The issue is solely that the \"Gemma 4\" model is too new for your current Ollama installation.\n\n### 2. How to fix Gemma 4 support\nIf Llama 3.1 works, you have two options to get Gemma 4 working:\n\n**Option A: Update your Nixpkgs (The \"Standard\" Way)**\nIf you haven't updated your flake inputs or channels recently:\n```bash\n# Update flake inputs (if using flakes)\nnix flake update --commit-lock-file /home/nondeus/.nix-config\n\n# Rebuild\nsudo nixos-rebuild switch --flake /home/nondeus/.nix-config\n```\n\n**Option B: Use the `ollama-cuda` from the \"unstable\" or \"master\" branch**\nIf the version in your current channel is stuck at 0.23.1, you may need to pull a newer version specifically for the Ollama package in your `configuration.nix`. \n\n**Would you like me to check your `flake.nix` or channel configuration to see if we can pull a more recent version (e.g., 0.24.x or 0.25.x) that might support Gemma 4?**","thoughts":[{"subject":"Investigating Gemma Support","description":"My current focus is on resolving the `unknown model architecture: 'gemma4'` error. It appears that Ollama version 0.23.1, even with its recent release date, does not yet recognize this particular Gemma architecture. I'm reconfirming the release timelines.","timestamp":"2026-05-21T01:25:52.144Z"},{"subject":"Verifying Ollama Version","description":"I'm now investigating if a newer Ollama version might resolve the `gemma4` architecture issue. It's possible the current 0.23.1 is too old, or the model itself is custom and not yet merged. I'll check the Nixpkgs channel for the latest available Ollama package.","timestamp":"2026-05-21T01:25:52.144Z"}],"tokens":{"input":50371,"output":447,"cached":46672,"thoughts":447,"tool":0,"total":51265},"model":"gemini-3-flash-preview"}
