{"id":"ab4cc58c-f82f-4d5e-bac8-24977e5e649c","timestamp":"2026-05-21T01:31:24.537Z","type":"gemini","content":"The \"Blue Screen\" followed by a TPM/CPU warning and Hyprland errors means your system had a significant kernel or GPU crash during the update process. \n\n### 1. The TPM / \"New CPU\" Warning\nThis is a common BIOS-level false alarm on modern motherboards (especially ASUS) after a hard freeze or force-reboot. Since you didn't actually swap your CPU, the motherboard simply detected a \"dirty\" state and reset its security flags. It is safe to proceed.\n\n### 2. Hyprland Config Errors\nYour update moved you to a very recent version of Hyprland that has deprecated or removed the `ignore_window` and `vfr` options. I have removed these from your source configuration in `~/.nix-config/dots/hypr/hyprland/general.conf`.\n\n### 3. Why is Ollama \"Old\"?\nWhile your kernel (7.0.5) is bleeding edge, packages like Ollama often lag behind in Nixpkgs because they require extensive testing with specific NVIDIA (CUDA) and AMD (ROCm) drivers. The version you have (0.23.1) is the current \"stable\" version for NixOS, even if Ollama upstream has newer releases.\n\n---\n\n### **Action: Run your rebuild now**\nI have fixed the configuration errors in your source files. Running a rebuild now will clear the Hyprland error bar and apply the changes cleanly:\n\n```bash\n# Run your standard rebuild command, e.g.:\nsudo nixos-rebuild switch --flake /home/nondeus/.nix-config\n```\n\n**Note:** Since I killed the \"zombie\" process earlier, this rebuild should finish without the \"status 4\" error you saw last time. Once it finishes, the Hyprland red bar should disappear.","thoughts":[{"subject":"Initiating Rebuild Protocol","description":"I'm preparing to instruct you on initiating a clean system rebuild. This is crucial now that the `asus-shutdown` zombie process has been resolved and configuration discrepancies have been rectified within the source code.","timestamp":"2026-05-21T01:31:22.126Z"}],"tokens":{"input":63461,"output":391,"cached":58751,"thoughts":274,"tool":0,"total":64126},"model":"gemini-3-flash-preview"}
