{"id":"8f1cb46a-348e-480d-93d0-07312d2f5dde","timestamp":"2026-05-21T01:32:51.076Z","type":"gemini","content":"","thoughts":[{"subject":"Resolving Model Architecture Error","description":"I've identified the core issue: Ollama's internal `llama.cpp` version doesn't recognize the 'gemma4' architecture. My focus is now on updating or configuring `llama.cpp` within Ollama to support this new model type.","timestamp":"2026-05-21T01:32:50.935Z"}],"tokens":{"input":65919,"output":33,"cached":62668,"thoughts":196,"tool":0,"total":66148},"model":"gemini-3-flash-preview","toolCalls":[{"id":"read_file_1779327170935_0","name":"read_file","args":{"file_path":"/home/nondeus/.nix-config/flake.nix"},"result":[{"functionResponse":{"id":"read_file_1779327170935_0","name":"read_file","response":{"output":"{\n  description = \"Infernal NixOS - Imprecation & Impermanence. [github.com/lowcache/infernalnixos.git]\";\n  inputs = {\n    nixpkgs.url = \"github:nixos/nixpkgs/nixos-unstable\";\n    home-manager = {\n      url = \"github:nix-community/home-manager\";\n      inputs.nixpkgs.follows = \"nixpkgs\";\n    };\n    nixos-hardware.url = \"github:NixOS/nixos-hardware/master\";\n    nix-cachyos-kernel.url = \"github:xddxdd/nix-cachyos-kernel\";\n    impermanence.url = \"github:nix-community/impermanence\";\n    lanzaboote = {\n      url = \"github:nix-community/lanzaboote\";\n      inputs.nixpkgs.follows = \"nixpkgs\";\n    };\n    microvm = {\n      url = \"github:astro/microvm.nix\";\n      inputs.nixpkgs.follows = \"nixpkgs\";\n    };\n    quickshell = {\n      url = \"git+https://git.outfoxxed.me/outfoxxed/quickshell\";\n      inputs.nixpkgs.follows = \"nixpkgs\";\n    };\n    lix-module = {\n      url = \"git+https://git.lix.systems/lix-project/nixos-module\";\n      inputs.nixpkgs.follows = \"nixpkgs\";\n      inputs.lix.url = \"git+https://git.lix.systems/lix-project/lix\";\n    };\n    sops-nix = {\n      url = \"github:Mic92/sops-nix\";\n      inputs.nixpkgs.follows = \"nixpkgs\";\n    };\n    infernal-init = {\n      url = \"github:lowcache/infernal-init\";\n      inputs.nixpkgs.follows = \"nixpkgs\";\n    };\n  };\n\n  outputs = { self, nixpkgs, home-manager, microvm, infernal-init, ... }@inputs: {\n    nixosConfigurations.nondeus = nixpkgs.lib.nixosSystem {\n      specialArgs = { inherit inputs; };\n      modules = [\n        { nixpkgs.hostPlatform = \"x86_64-linux\"; }\n        { nixpkgs.overlays = [ inputs.nix-cachyos-kernel.overlays.pinned ]; }\n        ./nixos/configuration.nix\n        ./nixos/hardware-configuration.nix\n        inputs.lanzaboote.nixosModules.lanzaboote\n        inputs.impermanence.nixosModules.impermanence\n        inputs.lix-module.nixosModules.default\n        inputs.sops-nix.nixosModules.sops\n        home-manager.nixosModules.home-manager\n        {\n          home-manager.useGlobalPkgs = true;\n          home-manager.useUserPackages = true;\n          home-manager.extraSpecialArgs = { inherit inputs; };\n          home-manager.users.nondeus = import ./home;\n        }\n      ];\n    };\n\n    # Add this to allow building/running the VM package\n    packages.x86_64-linux.net-gate = self.nixosConfigurations.nondeus.config.microvm.vms.net-gate.config.microvm.declaredRunner;\n  };\n}\n"}}}],"status":"success","timestamp":"2026-05-21T01:32:51.089Z","resultDisplay":"","description":".nix-config/flake.nix","displayName":"ReadFile","renderOutputAsMarkdown":true}]}
{"id":"f4bb5a6c-75ed-48ce-ae8c-298dd72aa30a","timestamp":"2026-05-21T01:32:57.516Z","type":"gemini","content":"I have definitely removed the `ignore_window` and `vfr` lines from your config files this time.\n\n### 1. Fix the Hyprland Errors\nBecause your configuration is managed by NixOS, the actual file at `~/.config/hypr/...` is a read-only symlink. Even though I edited the \"source\" file in your `.nix-config` folder, **you must run a rebuild** for Hyprland to see the changes.\n\nPlease run this now to clear the red error bars:\n```bash\nsudo nixos-rebuild switch --flake /home/nondeus/.nix-config\n```\n\n### 2. Ollama vs. llama.cpp\nYou don't necessarily need a different service, but you might want to use a different **engine** within Jan.\n\n*   **Ollama:** Is a wrapper around `llama.cpp`. If your system Ollama (v0.23.1) doesn't support \"Gemma 4\" yet, it's because that specific build hasn't integrated the latest architecture updates from upstream `llama.cpp`.\n*   **Jan's internal llama.cpp:** Jan AI comes with its own built-in `llama.cpp` engine (`@janhq/llamacpp-extension`). Since Jan often updates its internal engine independently of your system packages, it might actually be newer than the one in your Ollama service.\n\n**Try this:**\n1. In Jan AI, go to the **Hub**.\n2. Instead of using the \"Ollama\" provider, try to **Import** the GGUF model file directly from your storage:\n   `~/Storage/ollama/models/blobs/sha256-8193...`\n3. When you run it, ensure the **Inference Engine** is set to **llama.cpp** (not Ollama).\n\n### Why is Ollama \"old\" on Unstable?\nEven on `nixos-unstable`, the maintainers sometimes hold back complex packages like Ollama to ensure the CUDA/NVIDIA driver integration doesn't break. If you really need the absolute bleeding-edge Ollama (e.g. v0.25+), we could modify your `flake.nix` to pull it directly from the Ollama GitHub, but trying it directly in Jan's internal engine is much faster and safer for now.","thoughts":[{"subject":"Verifying Ollama Version","description":"I'm confirming if the installed Ollama version aligns with `nixos-unstable`'s latest builds. It appears 0.23.1 is indeed the most recently pushed version, which is expected for an unstable channel.","timestamp":"2026-05-21T01:32:54.138Z"}],"tokens":{"input":66989,"output":514,"cached":62692,"thoughts":127,"tool":0,"total":67630},"model":"gemini-3-flash-preview"}
{"$set":{"lastUpdated":"2026-05-21T01:32:57.517Z"}}
