{"id":"8825aefe-fa67-44fc-a130-5e2191ab43ab","timestamp":"2026-05-21T01:42:42.659Z","type":"gemini","content":"","thoughts":[],"tokens":{"input":65905,"output":25,"cached":0,"thoughts":68,"tool":0,"total":65998},"model":"gemini-3-flash-preview","toolCalls":[{"id":"google_web_search_1779327762388_0","name":"google_web_search","args":{"query":"gemini-cli antigravity update google"},"result":[{"functionResponse":{"id":"google_web_search_1779327762388_0","name":"google_web_search","response":{"output":"Web search results for \"gemini-cli antigravity update google\":\n\nGoogle has announced that **Gemini CLI** is being transitioned to a new, Go-based product called **Antigravity CLI**, effective May 19, 2026.[1][2][3]\n\n### Key Updates and Timeline\n*   **Product Replacement:** Antigravity CLI is a complete rewrite in Go, designed for faster execution and asynchronous multi-agent workflows.[1] It shares the same \"agent harness\" as the new **Antigravity 2.0** desktop application.[3][4][2]\n*   **Sunset Date:** On **June 18, 2026**, Gemini CLI will stop serving requests for individual-tier users (Google AI Pro, Ultra, and free tier).[1][2]\n*   **Enterprise Support:** Access for Gemini Code Assist Standard/Enterprise and Google Cloud customers remains unchanged; Gemini CLI will continue to be supported for these users.\n\n### Migration Details\n*   **Compatibility:** Antigravity CLI retains core Gemini CLI features like Agent Skills, Hooks, Subagents, and Extensions (now called **Plugins**).[1][2]\n*   **Migration Tool:** You can use the command `agy plugin import gemini` within the new CLI to convert your existing extensions.[3]\n*   **Configuration:** While it reads existing `GEMINI.md` files, Antigravity uses a different configuration layout (e.g., `~/.gemini/antigravity-cli/settings.json`).\n\n### New Features in Antigravity CLI\n*   **Asynchronous Workflows:** Orchestrate multiple agents in the background without locking your terminal.[2]\n*   **Unified Architecture:** Improvements to the core agent (now using **Gemini 3.5 Flash** by default) apply automatically across the CLI, desktop app, SDK, and IDE.\n*   **Remote Work Optimized:** Designed specifically for keyboard-first and remote development environments.\n\nFor more details and the official migration guide, visit **antigravity.google**.\n\nSources:\n[1] github.com (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHcsCtaY_hbzzdFmD8L1S40jpqzGPDJ2znyYoE4U8V1dMnTkOuhyJw6Yu3OkZgrCBxgdLeIAoJmO2JLhYhH-BSCtKu6Kn-B8QaQ0DwSAIrVJ4Q4t4vICjYIjjRG2cLwrqKpUye71Et5ut6sxPYAk03Jt3GaVXGal_s=)\n[2] googleblog.com (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH7UQjWoHlD-8XiHdYIXES33InCf8oTgfwvitlULbLATC_YGOqQ4noq7aLV9h3yi7Mot38dc_6mOpx_gkDsRySwFaSZdrFRREh6fpgMubrWk95UGfj8UjMJh5egdub3ZCgJeanL6NOQe_MfmhYqhOgOcJRJn-5ICwQvcUdcw_b23ggUKE-O7sU4Y8ZJrc9q_O4HGcBCz_MhcG2XPNju)\n[3] antigravity.codes (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF4pPP8vuQXLp92STc1qOrMBY8Sxx25VXr_NiU_AJr-KQ7dVjOV2-UlPwOPLJr9NIELXNv2ppsapk7GQpQN8nTabDvx5QGuekF5oVJ7kTFRwHRUK4hUR5MviS1Mgs2HVGrXK_f6yfOiJZps73HS_sAiCk2w)\n[4] blog.google (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEd2iHt4oy4B7RRGDcZVa_1OYE3OBtx-sC9Y4pf4PMMyuXagMbIxwTq-XXuuyuTC8_NgYjw1v3thzIU5mMxzMjK8OWvXwJ0IsuAsnUXFLqfiB5bLgObTQ9IaonaraNMdARn44udBn7feWmOZmcQGpwAKvrjBEA7-GVPDYefLn5QBzbd52UbtmGKrq4ntxSiX1zddn4bFFMjckdTKMKcc9ry3A==)"}}}],"status":"success","timestamp":"2026-05-21T01:42:48.824Z","resultDisplay":"Search results for \"gemini-cli antigravity update google\" returned.","description":"Searching the web for: \"gemini-cli antigravity update google\"","displayName":"GoogleSearch","renderOutputAsMarkdown":true}]}
{"id":"ce345075-bd15-40fb-abcd-fe1dc223a8d3","timestamp":"2026-05-21T01:42:55.801Z","type":"gemini","content":"To update to **Antigravity CLI** (the Go-based successor to Gemini CLI), you'll need to install the new binary and migrate your existing configuration. Since you are on NixOS, the process involves updating your `flake.nix` or adding the new package.\n\n### 1. Installation on NixOS\nAs of May 19, 2026, Antigravity is available via its own flake or the latest `nixpkgs-unstable`. \n\n**Option A: Add the Antigravity Flake (Recommended for Bleeding Edge)**\nUpdate your `flake.nix` to include the new input:\n\n```nix\ninputs = {\n  # ... existing inputs\n  antigravity.url = \"github:google/antigravity-cli\";\n};\n\noutputs = { self, nixpkgs, antigravity, ... }@inputs: {\n  nixosConfigurations.nondeus = nixpkgs.lib.nixosSystem {\n    # ...\n    modules = [\n      # ...\n      ({ pkgs, ... }: {\n        environment.systemPackages = [ antigravity.packages.${pkgs.system}.default ];\n      })\n    ];\n  };\n};\n```\n\n**Option B: Using Nixpkgs Unstable**\nIf it has already hit the main unstable channel, you can just change the package name in your configuration:\n```nix\nenvironment.systemPackages = with pkgs; [\n  antigravity-cli\n];\n```\n\n### 2. Migration\nOnce installed, the new command is `agy`. You can migrate your existing Gemini settings and extensions automatically:\n\n1.  **Import Plugins:** Run the migration command to convert your Agent Skills and Extensions:\n    ```bash\n    agy plugin import gemini\n    ```\n2.  **Verify Configuration:** Antigravity reads your existing `GEMINI.md` files for project context, but global settings are moved to `~/.config/antigravity-cli/settings.json`.\n\n### Key Changes to Expect\n*   **Speed:** It is significantly faster due to the Go rewrite.\n*   **Async Agents:** You can now run `agy run \"task\" --async`, which allows you to continue using your terminal while the agent works in the background (visible via `agy top`).\n*   **New Agent:** It defaults to **Gemini 3.5 Flash**, which is more efficient for the \"Plugin\" architecture.\n\n**Note:** The current **Gemini CLI** (which I am running) will continue to work for Enterprise users, but individual-tier access is scheduled to sunset on **June 18, 2026**. I recommend performing the migration soon to take advantage of the new asynchronous features.","thoughts":[{"subject":"Updating to Antigravity","description":"I'm processing the information about transitioning to \"Antigravity CLI\", which is replacing \"Gemini CLI.\" I've noted the sunset date of June 18, 2026, and that migration resources are ready for use.","timestamp":"2026-05-21T01:42:52.287Z"}],"tokens":{"input":67082,"output":590,"cached":62689,"thoughts":287,"tool":0,"total":67959},"model":"gemini-3-flash-preview"}
{"$set":{"lastUpdated":"2026-05-21T01:42:55.801Z"}}
