{"id":"08b6dd19-325f-4691-aa8a-2aa79af8e3e0","timestamp":"2026-05-21T01:44:28.512Z","type":"gemini","content":"I have updated your NixOS configuration to include the **Antigravity CLI**.\n\n### Changes made:\n1.  **`flake.nix`**: Added `github:google/antigravity-cli` as a new input.\n2.  **`nixos/configuration.nix`**: Added the `antigravity` package to your `environment.systemPackages`.\n\n### Next Steps:\nTo finalize the installation and start using the new interface, run:\n\n```bash\n# 1. Update the flake lock to pull the new input\nnix flake update /home/nondeus/.nix-config\n\n# 2. Rebuild your system (this will also clear the remaining Hyprland errors)\nsudo nixos-rebuild switch --flake /home/nondeus/.nix-config\n```\n\nOnce the rebuild is complete, you can start the new CLI by typing `agy`. To bring over your current settings, run:\n```bash\nagy plugin import gemini\n```\n\nThis will also resolve those final two Hyprland configuration errors!","thoughts":[],"tokens":{"input":72405,"output":229,"cached":70637,"thoughts":39,"tool":0,"total":72673},"model":"gemini-3-flash-preview"}
