{"id":"e8e5833a-fa19-4af7-a64d-99beee10d686","timestamp":"2026-05-21T01:46:07.616Z","type":"gemini","content":"","thoughts":[{"subject":"Investigating Flake Failures","description":"I'm currently troubleshooting a recent build failure on NixOS. It seems adding the `antigravity` flake input triggered a 404 error from GitHub, indicating a problem with accessing the repository. I'm looking into the specifics of this HTTP error to resolve the issue.","timestamp":"2026-05-21T01:46:07.268Z"}],"tokens":{"input":71739,"output":140,"cached":66688,"thoughts":327,"tool":0,"total":72206},"model":"gemini-3-flash-preview","toolCalls":[{"id":"update_topic_1779327967426_0","name":"update_topic","args":{"summary":"The rebuild failed with a 404 error because the guessed GitHub URL for Antigravity CLI was incorrect. I am now searching for the official installation URL or the correct GitHub repository path for Antigravity CLI (announced May 19, 2026) to fix the flake input.","strategic_intent":"Correcting the Antigravity CLI repository URL and resolving the rebuild error.","title":"Fixing Antigravity CLI Installation URL"},"result":[{"functionResponse":{"id":"update_topic_1779327967426_0","name":"update_topic","response":{"output":"Current topic: \"Fixing Antigravity CLI Installation URL\"\nTopic summary: The rebuild failed with a 404 error because the guessed GitHub URL for Antigravity CLI was incorrect. I am now searching for the official installation URL or the correct GitHub repository path for Antigravity CLI (announced May 19, 2026) to fix the flake input.\n\nStrategic Intent: Correcting the Antigravity CLI repository URL and resolving the rebuild error."}}}],"status":"success","timestamp":"2026-05-21T01:46:13.328Z","resultDisplay":"## 📂 Topic: **Fixing Antigravity CLI Installation URL**\n\n**Summary:**\nThe rebuild failed with a 404 error because the guessed GitHub URL for Antigravity CLI was incorrect. I am now searching for the official installation URL or the correct GitHub repository path for Antigravity CLI (announced May 19, 2026) to fix the flake input.\n\n> [!STRATEGY]\n> **Intent:** Correcting the Antigravity CLI repository URL and resolving the rebuild error.","description":"Update topic to: \"Fixing Antigravity CLI Installation URL\"","displayName":"Update Topic Context","renderOutputAsMarkdown":true},{"id":"google_web_search_1779327967448_1","name":"google_web_search","args":{"query":"antigravity-cli github repository google gemini migration"},"result":[{"functionResponse":{"id":"google_web_search_1779327967448_1","name":"google_web_search","response":{"output":"Web search results for \"antigravity-cli github repository google gemini migration\":\n\n[ESTABLISHED] Google has officially announced the migration of **Gemini CLI** to the new **Antigravity CLI** as part of the broader **Antigravity 2.0** platform.[1][2][3] This transition was unveiled at Google I/O 2026 on May 19, 2026.[3][1]\n\n### Key Migration Details\n*   **Deadline:** Gemini CLI and Gemini Code Assist IDE extensions will stop serving requests for free and individual users (AI Pro, Ultra, and free tiers) on **June 18, 2026**.[4][5][1][3][2]\n*   **Enterprise Exception:** Organizations with Gemini Code Assist Standard or Enterprise licenses can continue using Gemini CLI with no immediate changes.[3][4][5]\n*   **Core Changes:**\n    *   **Language:** Antigravity CLI is built in **Go** (replacing the Node.js-based Gemini CLI) for faster execution and lower overhead.[3]\n    *   **Architecture:** It supports **asynchronous multi-agent workflows**, allowing multiple agents to run in the background simultaneously.[3][4][5]\n    *   **Open Source Status:** Unlike the open-source Gemini CLI (which had over 100,000 stars), Antigravity CLI is currently **closed-source**.[3]\n\n### Migration Steps for Users\n1.  **Installation:** Install the new CLI (refer to `antigravity.google` for the official download).\n2.  **Configuration:** Rename your context files from `GEMINI.md` to `.antigravity.md`.[3]\n3.  **Skills & Agents:**\n    *   Global skills in `~/.gemini/skills/` are shared and picked up automatically.[6]\n    *   Workspace-specific skills should be moved from `.gemini/skills/` to `.agents/skills/`.\n    *   Agent YAML files should be moved from `.gemini/agents/` to `.antigravity/agents/`.[3]\n4.  **Plugins:** Gemini CLI \"Extensions\" are now called \"Plugins.\"[6][1][4] You can import them using:\n    ```bash\n    agy plugin import gemini\n    ```[6]\n\n### Repository Information\nThe original Gemini CLI repository remains on GitHub (Apache 2.0 license) for enterprise maintenance, but active consumer development has shifted to the proprietary Antigravity platform. Official documentation and the SDK can be found at **antigravity.google**.\n\nSources:\n[1] virtualizationreview.com (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGbP9q2lOJgUXF7QdujqPw9iWRb1B_1cCeUE3rONmLxrO7rshOiVEoCOpx06YLefbr2bHB3qUmp6sy3tovjrFrpgAR-sDLNvd6D0IcDqDbfr6YVLn1nSy1DuZxi6cIb7pSDSUS-fu-bq1JCXUI7-ZQiLeDkMvvXn2MBA9TmGajzkIvgwPuyxTVE_sDNztpu62YXfW5KfKoj4-MZn14La8OzSJiQ6RzTqXT789wbz782Ely1jPzPdoPSj35m2A==)\n[2] techradar.com (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFspEOvNE8zj9dUVkc6FfaM6SkJyESFUVk4FQz74GdXWNWEotOZZzH1DwxxNgtUnrcORjtcP32y1Va6YvSkEYZre05yvaLKiTGRh-14mfDyvRbdnEW_nQQBkuz_mNnM1bk0xmGfX3bTq97CJ7Kz5BKk1faNVQx1Yv5Yy1tjN58XCbvv4Od2DbHjhYyrO_ou8_KzkESyzinmM_RuzmmR-gcHSyWQbWLCb1t3getVHUyYqjWQj69vvP3fpQ==)\n[3] medium.com (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHGuVoP7voNVBVakdeQeVMR15ecep4nN_iFRfmUzIhMlhOITRF9DHZL6xcjj89SfUKu9dni4UIa438j2ei4ETws-Zob1nNgya7U-SDa-4SO9aQNAwMvtjJpz10iBc6rKoxNO8CQPPDwHXHphoo67RtqqlcropfsfLT6kXZ57ITyClYa_Y5ECaexRMYo9pPbZXnW_WBYnjYRk3x9zHV5TQEVhNVrYJG6SjltAKQ=)\n[4] googleblog.com (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHLrD2eG2cuos1v84SaVWa4liJ9Lvwu6PCZPXmyg1a_aPBJs3grpisgkTHosfbYLAagt9OmXbwM2xpeGhdXRTmbVe7pvODjzVfXmmATwd2SarDwF0dVXlFV30WNFuUIw1lO0ud5XyX57wnGljWQ8UeBlorJYNkPEZfUbww2F0d04A6FOtpOt0mt51Zh2aQgL7VNo2KdnbI-B7sXa3DU)\n[5] letsdatascience.com (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHpLfxCit-Jhk_j8ljAlpOuD_i6px3FuiqnL3y_ag5dl74WXxN26KDinldI_CwstVS99hVmFUd2gChGxkEpGId4z64VQ6v21g0GAkcvr0oGqydam2WoRDEtQvqFCJOs-u1QccGQkfr9v_cfWLehlSUIeX26O4-LvwqIHSos7R_fEohIxhD-PKSTkiljlrBs52aOFMa5)\n[6] antigravity.google (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF61ykHCbNs6imjhHy-kK3qS_7hAtQ-dA73OH1eXDnyrYdM6LlrBBZTRZ5MFBPeyRqR8YRTO4snIUj2Z0ZIj6Okc7qOa-ZY2p7wZsuDWqqjqAcsZj8Z0ZU3k25Q0i9Cs45YTPHcVLBByZQ=)"}}}],"status":"success","timestamp":"2026-05-21T01:46:13.328Z","resultDisplay":"Search results for \"antigravity-cli github repository google gemini migration\" returned.","description":"Searching the web for: \"antigravity-cli github repository google gemini migration\"","displayName":"GoogleSearch","renderOutputAsMarkdown":true}]}
{"id":"ba654ab7-79d6-4eae-9e76-9e79529e7745","timestamp":"2026-05-21T01:46:19.270Z","type":"gemini","content":"The 404 error occurred because **Antigravity CLI is currently closed-source**, meaning it does not have a public GitHub repository that can be added as a Nix flake input.\n\nI apologize for the oversight. Since it is proprietary, we cannot install it via a GitHub flake. Instead, you'll need to use the binary installation method provided by Google.\n\n### Step 1: Revert the Flake Changes\nWe need to revert the changes to your `flake.nix` and `configuration.nix` so your system can rebuild cleanly again.\n\n1.  **Revert `flake.nix`:** Remove the `antigravity` input.\n2.  **Revert `nixos/configuration.nix`:** Remove `inputs.antigravity.packages.${pkgs.system}.default` from your system packages.\n\n### Step 2: Install Antigravity CLI (Binary Method)\nSince there isn't an official Nix package yet, the best way to use it on NixOS is to download the binary and use your existing `nix-ld` configuration (which I see is already enabled in your `configuration.nix`) to run it.\n\n1.  Go to **[antigravity.google](https://antigravity.google)** and download the Linux x86_64 binary.\n2.  Place the `agy` binary in your `~/.local/bin/` directory.\n3.  Make it executable: `chmod +x ~/.local/bin/agy`.\n\n### Step 3: Migration\nOnce the binary is in your path, run the migration:\n```bash\nagy plugin import gemini\n```\n\n---\n\n**I will now revert the broken Nix configuration for you so you can fix those Hyprland errors.**\n[Thought: true]","thoughts":[],"tokens":{"input":73970,"output":698,"cached":70657,"thoughts":0,"tool":0,"total":74668},"model":"gemini-3-flash-preview"}
