{"id":"ba654ab7-79d6-4eae-9e76-9e79529e7745","timestamp":"2026-05-21T01:46:19.270Z","type":"gemini","content":"The 404 error occurred because **Antigravity CLI is currently closed-source**, meaning it does not have a public GitHub repository that can be added as a Nix flake input.\n\nI apologize for the oversight. Since it is proprietary, we cannot install it via a GitHub flake. Instead, you'll need to use the binary installation method provided by Google.\n\n### Step 1: Revert the Flake Changes\nWe need to revert the changes to your `flake.nix` and `configuration.nix` so your system can rebuild cleanly again.\n\n1.  **Revert `flake.nix`:** Remove the `antigravity` input.\n2.  **Revert `nixos/configuration.nix`:** Remove `inputs.antigravity.packages.${pkgs.system}.default` from your system packages.\n\n### Step 2: Install Antigravity CLI (Binary Method)\nSince there isn't an official Nix package yet, the best way to use it on NixOS is to download the binary and use your existing `nix-ld` configuration (which I see is already enabled in your `configuration.nix`) to run it.\n\n1.  Go to **[antigravity.google](https://antigravity.google)** and download the Linux x86_64 binary.\n2.  Place the `agy` binary in your `~/.local/bin/` directory.\n3.  Make it executable: `chmod +x ~/.local/bin/agy`.\n\n### Step 3: Migration\nOnce the binary is in your path, run the migration:\n```bash\nagy plugin import gemini\n```\n\n---\n\n**I will now revert the broken Nix configuration for you so you can fix those Hyprland errors.**\n[Thought: true]","thoughts":[],"tokens":{"input":73970,"output":698,"cached":70657,"thoughts":0,"tool":0,"total":74668},"model":"gemini-3-flash-preview","toolCalls":[{"id":"replace_1779327978974_0","name":"replace","args":{"instruction":"Revert the broken Antigravity CLI flake input.","file_path":"/home/nondeus/.nix-config/flake.nix","old_string":"    infernal-init = {\n      url = \"github:lowcache/infernal-init\";\n      inputs.nixpkgs.follows = \"nixpkgs\";