{"id":"b05f33ae-0cc8-4095-9ee2-5aadc9573987","timestamp":"2026-05-21T02:57:23.038Z","type":"gemini","content":"I have reverted the broken flake configuration. You can now run your rebuild command, which will finish cleanly and resolve the Hyprland errors:\n\n```bash\nsudo nixos-rebuild switch --flake /home/nondeus/.nix-config\n```\n\n### Summary of what happened:\n*   **The 404 Error:** Google announced Antigravity as a proprietary (closed-source) replacement. It doesn't have a public GitHub repository, which is why the flake input failed.\n*   **Hyprland Errors:** These are still there because the last rebuild failed. Once you run the command above, they will disappear.\n*   **Next for Antigravity:** To use the new interface, download the Linux binary from **antigravity.google** and place it in your path. Your existing `nix-ld` setup will allow it to run on NixOS without issues.","thoughts":[],"tokens":{"input":74882,"output":190,"cached":0,"thoughts":0,"tool":0,"total":75072},"model":"gemini-3-flash-preview"}
