{"id":"e63b485a-c75d-4c81-9709-d0dc1f8306e9","timestamp":"2026-05-21T03:32:16.969Z","type":"gemini","content":"**Resolving Antigravity Installation** I'm currently stuck on the Antigravity update. The earlier \"Option A\" failed because the repository is closed-source. I've searched the `Downloads` folder for an `agy` binary but found nothing. I'll need to provide clear instructions on how to manually acquire and install the binary on NixOS.\n[Thought: true]Since the **Antigravity CLI** is currently proprietary (closed-source), we cannot install it via a GitHub flake like we tried earlier. I've checked your Downloads folder and don't see the binary there yet.\n\nHere is the correct way to get it running on your NixOS system:\n\n### 1. Download the Binary\nGo to **[antigravity.google](https://antigravity.google)** and download the **Linux x86_64** binary.\n\n### 2. Install to your local path\nOnce downloaded, run these commands to put it in your user path and make it executable:\n```bash\n# Create the local bin directory if it doesn't exist\nmkdir -p ~/.local/bin\n\n# Move the binary from Downloads (assuming the filename is 'agy')\nmv ~/Downloads/agy ~/.local/bin/agy\n\n# Make it executable\nchmod +x ~/.local/bin/agy\n```\n\n### 3. Verify it works\nRun the version command to ensure it's working:\n```bash\nagy --version\n```\n\n### 4. Migrate your Gemini context\nTo bring over your current project context and skills:\n```bash\nagy plugin import gemini\n```\n\n---\n\n**Note on NixOS Compatibility:**\nBecause you already have `nix-ld` enabled in your `configuration.nix`, the `agy` binary should \"just work\" without you needing to do anything else. If you get a \"file not found\" or \"interpreter\" error when running it, let me know and I can help you create a **Nix wrapper** for it.\n\n**Would you like me to wait for you to download the file, or should we try to `curl` it directly if you can find the link?**","thoughts":[],"tokens":{"input":94028,"output":458,"cached":