{"id":"437f2f37-c71c-4c51-bdb8-59603eaeba4e","timestamp":"2026-05-21T03:36:13.420Z","type":"gemini","content":"The **Antigravity CLI** is now installed and working! I have also set up the **Antigravity Desktop** and **IDE** apps in your `~/AppImage` directory.\n\n### 1. The CLI is ready\nThe `agy` command is installed at `~/.local/bin/agy`. \n*   **To check the version:** `agy --version`\n*   **To migrate your Gemini project:** `agy plugin import gemini`\n\n### 2. Desktop & IDE Setup\nI have moved the extracted folders to:\n*   `~/AppImage/Antigravity`\n*   `~/AppImage/Antigravity IDE`\n\n**Important:** Because these are Electron-based apps running on NixOS, they need specific system libraries to be available via `nix-ld`. I have already updated your `configuration.nix` to include these missing libraries (`glib`, `atk`, `pango`, etc.).\n\n### 3. Final Step: Rebuild\nTo make the Desktop apps launchable and finalize the system cleanup, run:\n```bash\nsudo nixos-rebuild switch --flake /home/nondeus/.nix-config\n```\n\n### 4. Launching the Apps\nAfter the rebuild, you can launch them from your terminal (or I can help you create desktop shortcuts/icons once you've confirmed they open):\n```bash\n# Launch Antigravity\n~/AppImage/Antigravity/antigravity\n\n# Launch Antigravity IDE\n\"~/AppImage/Antigravity IDE/antigravity-ide\"\n```\n\n**Everything is now in place. Run the rebuild, and you'll be fully migrated to the Antigravity platform!**","thoughts":[],"tokens":{"input":103279,"output":367,"cached":102624,"thoughts":10,"tool":0,"total":103656},"model":"gemini-3-flash-preview"}
